<p>I'm working on a page that use the X-editable library with Bootstrap 3; I have multiples instances of plugins. But, for some cases, I need a custom button template, then I change that with global option:</p>  <pre><code>$.fn.editableform.buttons </code></pre>  <p>But this change all X-editable instances. Is there a way that I can customize only one instance? How can I write a jQuery plugin that extends the same as the original, but with my own default settings?</p>  <p>I tried this so far:</p>  <pre><code>(function($){     $.fn.customEditable = function(settings) {          this.editable = $.fn.editable(settings);         this.editable.editableform.buttons = '&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm editable-trigger"&gt;&lt;i class="glyphicon glyphicon-edit"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/button&gt;';          return this;     }; })(jQuery); </code></pre>